Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of reducing the domination number of a graph by one through edge contractions, which is a problem in graph theory. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem on various classes of graphs, indicating a focus on computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of claw-free graphs and $P_6$-free graphs, which are topics in graph theory and computational geometry, respectively, suggesting the sub-categories cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible choices.
